abstract: Bernie Sanders has a shot to deliver an embarrassing blow to Amy Klobuchar in the moderate senator's home state on Super Tuesday, thanks to a large and motivated progressive base in a state where she was once considered a shoo-in to win.

abstract: A.J. Broome is a 56-year-old married gay man living in St. Petersburg, Florida. Until recently, he was torn over who to pick in the Florida primary.

abstract: Democrats increasingly regard winning the Senate as their last remaining check on President Trump, should he win re-election, while Republicans fight to maintain power in Congress.
snippet: Democrats increasingly regard winning the Senate as their last remaining check on President Trump, should he win re-election, while Republicans fight to maintain power in Congress.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The 2020 battle for control of the Senate gets underway in earnest Tuesday, with both parties increasingly seeing the chamber as a must-win prize to guard against uncertainty over who will wind up in the White House.

abstract: Democratic presidential candidate Elizabeth Warren pulled in more than $29 million in February, according to a campaign memo released on Sunday, more in a single month than the campaign had raised in any previous quarter.
snippet: Democratic presidential candidate Elizabeth Warren pulled in more than $29 million in February, according to a campaign memo released on Sunday, more in a single month than the campaign had raised in any previous quarter.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Democratic presidential candidate Elizabeth Warren pulled in more than $29 million in February, according to a campaign memo released on Sunday, more in a single month than the campaign had raised in any previous quarter.

abstract: It isn't easy being a Bernie Sanders supporter in a conservative state like Oklahoma. Travis Wyman, a 40-year-old construction worker and online “social justice warrior,” says he and other Sanders fans can hear “fear-mongering words” like socialist and communist thrown at them many times a day.

headline_main: How the Democrats’ ‘15% Rule’ Could Reshape the Race on Super Tuesday

abstract: He needs to capitalize on his big South Carolina win to stay competitive with Bernie Sanders.
snippet: He needs to capitalize on his big South Carolina win to stay competitive with Bernie Sanders.
lead_paragraph: Finally! Four states and nearly two months into the Democratic primary voting, Joe Biden scored a win. On Saturday, he received a big electoral kiss from South Carolina, where he captured 48 percent of the vote and at least 29 of 54 delegates (with more expected as the results were finalized). It was the largest margin of victory — and the largest single delegate haul — in the race thus far.

abstract: Bernie Sanders' presidential campaign said Sunday that it raised more than $46.5 million in February, a show of financial strength after the Vermont senator finished a distant second behind Joe Biden in South Carolina's primary.
snippet: Bernie Sanders' presidential campaign said Sunday that it raised more than $46.5 million in February, a show of financial strength after the Vermont senator finished a distant second behind Joe Biden in South Carolina's primary.
lead_paragraph: VIRGINIA BEACH, Va. — Bernie Sanders' presidential campaign said Sunday that it raised more than $46.5 million in February, a show of financial strength after the Vermont senator finished a distant second behind Joe Biden in South Carolina's primary.
headline_main: Sanders Raised Stout $46.5M in February; Warren Got $29M
headline_print_headline: Sanders Raised Stout $46.5M in February; Warren Got $29M
